Steps of Running hello world with ocelot opencl library

1.Install SNU OpenCL Kernel compiler
tar -xzvf SnuCL-0.8.5.tar.gz
Follow the installation guide in SnuCL/README.txt to install SNUCL

2.Build hello world kernel
cd hello_world
../t-gpu.sh hello_world.cl

3.Rename kernel output to activate OpenCL runtime backdoor
mv hello_world.cl.ptx buildout.ptx

4.Build hello world host code, replace library path if necessary
g++ hello_world.cpp -o hello_world_ocelot -L$HOME/local/lib -locelot-opencl

5.Set up device
Open configure.ocelot
Edit "devices" item under "executive", choose llvm/emulated/nvidia as device
Save configure.ocelot

6. Run hello world
./hello_world_ocelot

